Pre-information and notice
In the case of construction projects with construction services to be awarded throughout Europe, the public builder must inform interested companies of the planned awards in advance of the tender.
Preliminary information and announcements form an important basis for Europe-wide competition.
Requirements of EU law and corruption prevention
The preliminary information is intended to contain the essential information on the planned construction projects under public procurement law.
They are required for those construction projects where the estimated total contract value reaches or exceeds the EU threshold and where the client wants to shorten the offer periods of open or non-open procedures.
In announcements, the client must provide more detailed information on the planned construction contracts to be awarded throughout Europe.
