The regulations of both countries regarding the opening of the bids are in agreement in relevant parts. They take into account both the principle of multi-eyes and the principle of transparency. Thus, the risks of corruption and manipulation can be significantly limited in the opening of the bids.
The requirements in Germany are more comprehensive than those in the Czech Republic.
In particular, the requirements for the exact documentation of the process as well as for the identification, safe custody and confidentiality of the offers significantly restrict the possibilities of manipulation, such as subsequent changes to the offers.
In addition, those responsible for opening the tenders are not allowed to carry out any other tasks in connection with the service to be awarded.
